label.value: histone H2AX kinase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group to a histone variant H2AX.

label.value: retrotransposon silencing by heterochromatin formation

value.value: A retrotransposon silencing mechanism involving heterochromatin assembly. Heterochromatin is a chromatin conformation that is refractory to transcription.

label.value: piRNA-mediated retrotransposon silencing by heterochromatin formation

value.value: A retrotransposon silencing mechanism in which a Piwi-associated RNA (piRNA) triggers heterochromatin assembly. Heterochromatin is a chromatin conformation that is refractory to transcription.

label.value: siRNA-mediated retrotransposon silencing by heterochromatin formation

value.value: A retrotransposon silencing mechanism in which a siRNA triggers heterochromatin assembly. Heterochromatin is a chromatin conformation that is refractory to transcription.

label.value: retrotransposon silencing by mRNA destabilization

value.value: A retrotransposon silencing mechanism in which mRNAs transcribed from transposons are targeted for degradation.

label.value: piRNA-mediated retrotransposon silencing by mRNA destabilization

value.value: A retrotransposon silencing mechanism in which mRNAs transcribed from transposons are targeted for degradation by a Piwi-associated RNA (piRNA).

label.value: retrotransposon silencing by siRNA-directed DNA methylation

value.value: A retrotransposon silencing mechanism mediated by RNA-directed DNA methylation. RNA-directed DNA methylation is a gene silencing process in which small interfering RNAs (siRNAs) guide DNA methylation to the siRNA-generating genomic loci and other loci that are homologous to the siRNAs for de novo DNA methylation. This results in a heterochromatin assembly, a chromatin conformation that is refractory to transcription.

label.value: siRNA-mediated retrotransposon silencing by mRNA destabilization

value.value: A retrotransposon silencing mechanism in which mRNAs transcribed from transposons are targeted for degradation by a siRNA.

label.value: purine nucleotide import into lysosome

value.value: The directed import of purine nucleotide from the cytosol, across the lysosomal membrane, into the lysosome.

label.value: ribosome hibernation

value.value: A cellular process that results in the silencing of ribosomes in quiescent cells. Quiescence takes place when cells encounter unfavorable conditions and cease to grow in bacteria and yeast. It also takes place in some specialized cells in higher eukaryotes, such as eggs. Ribosomes in a hibernation state are kept silent via association with proteins with inhibitory and protective functions.

label.value: G/T mismatch-specific thymine-DNA glycosylase activity

value.value: Hydrolyzes mismatched double-stranded DNA and polynucleotides, releasing free thymine and leaving an apyrimidinic (AP) site.

label.value: effector-mediated induction of cell cycle reactivation in host

value.value: A symbiont process in which a molecule secreted by the symbiont reactivates the host cell cycle, resulting in DNA synthesis and host cell division, and contributing to vegetative tumor formation.

label.value: adhesion of symbiont to host via host extracellular matrix

value.value: The attachment of a symbiont to its host by binding to a component of the host extracellular matrix. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: symbiont-mediated disruption of host cell-cell adhesion

value.value: A process in which a symbiont alters or subverts host cell adhesion ito its extracellular matrix. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: adhesion of symbiont to host cell surface via host membrane carbohydrate

value.value: The attachment of a symbiont to its host by binding to a carbohydrate on the host cell surface. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: adhesion of symbiont to host cell surface via host glycoprotein

value.value: The attachment of a symbiont to its host by binding to a glycoprotein on the host cell surface. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: adhesion of symbiont to host cell surface via host membrane cholesterol

value.value: The attachment of a symbiont to its host by binding to cholesterol on the host cell surface. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host actin cytoskeleton

value.value: The process in which an organism effects a change that impairs the structure or function of the host actin cytoskeleton. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host microtubule cytoskeleton

value.value: The process in which an organism effects a change that impairs the structure or function of the host microtubule cytoskeleton. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: symbiont-mediated disruption of host focal adhesion

value.value: A process in which a symbiont alters or subverts focal adhesion in its host. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host actin cytoskeleton via filamentous actin depolymerization

value.value: The process in which an organism effects a change that impairs the structure or function of the host actin cytoskeleton by depolymerizing the host filamentous actin. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host actin cytoskeleton via actin crosslinking

value.value: The process in which an organism effects a change that impairs the structure or function of the host actin cytoskeleton by actin crosslinking the host actin filaments. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host actin cytoskeleton via actin filament reorganization

value.value: The process in which an organism effects a change that impairs the structure or function of the host actin cytoskeleton by reorganizing the actin filaments, in a way that keeps the total filementous actin remains approximately constant. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host actin cytoskeleton via actin polymerization

value.value: The process in which an organism effects a change that impairs the structure or function of the host actin cytoskeleton by polymerizing the host filamentous actin. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host actin cytoskeleton via inhibition of actin polymerization

value.value: The process in which an organism effects a change that disrupts the host actin cytoskeleton by inhibiting host actin from polymerizing. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: CTP-dependent diacylglycerol kinase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: a 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol + CTP = a 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate + CDP + H+.

label.value: phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase activator activity

value.value: Binds to and increases the activity of a phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase (PI3K).

label.value: phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase inhibitor activity

value.value: Binds to and decreases the activity of a phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase (PI3K).

label.value: very-long-chain 3-oxoacyl-CoA reductase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: a very-long-chain (3R)-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA + NADP+ = a very-long-chain 3-oxoacyl-CoA + H+ + NADPH. This reaction is the second (reduction) step of the four-step fatty acid elongation cycle in the endoplasmic reticulum that extends fatty acids of C-16 or longer with an additional 2-C unit.

label.value: disruption of extracellular matrix of another organism

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways performed by an organism resulting in the breakdown of the extracellular matrix of another organism.

definition.value: Note that this process can occur during host-symbiont interactions or be mediated by toxin secreted by free-living organisms.

label.value: symbiont-mediated cAMP intoxication of host cell

value.value: The production by a symbiont of high levels of cyclic AMP in a host cell, impairing host cellular functions in multiple ways, including ATP depletion, interference with host intracellular signaling, cytoskeletal defects and apoptosis-related cell death. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: symbiont-mediated evasion of host innate immune response

value.value: A process by which a symbiont avoids recognition by host's innate immune response by altering, concealing or destroying a conserved symbiont molecule recognized by the host. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: epigenetic programming in the endosperm

value.value: The global programming of epigenetic modifications following binucleate central cell fertilization. This involves DNA methylation at the silent allele. In the endosperm, maternal genomes are hypomethylated compared with the paternal genome.

label.value: Atg8-family conjugating enzyme activity

value.value: Isoenergetic transfer of an Atg8 family modifier from one protein to a phosphatidylethanolamine or phosphatidylserine on a membrane, via the reaction X-Atg8 + Y = Y-Atg8 + X.

label.value: molecular tag activity

value.value: A molecular function exhibited by a protein that is covalently attached (AKA tagged or conjugated) to another molecule (for example a protein or a lipid) where it acts as a marker, recognized by the cellular apparatus to target the tagged protein for some cellular process such as modification, sequestration, transport or degradation.

definition.value: Use this term to annotate conjugated tags, not for conjugating enzymes. At the time of writing, all known gene products with this activity are ubiquitin-like, either based on overall sequence similarity or the presence of common motifs and structures.

label.value: membrane tag activity

value.value: A molecular function exhibited by a protein that is covalently attached (AKA tagged or conjugated) to a lipid, where it acts as a marker for a membrane, recognized by the cellular apparatus to target the tagged protein for some cellular process such as autophagy.

definition.value: Use this term to annotate conjugated tags, not for conjugating enzymes. At the time of writing, all known gene products with this activity are ubiquitin-like, either based on overall sequence similarity or the presence of common motifs and structures.

label.value: protein-glutathione oxidoreductase (glutathione) activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: glutathionylated protein (PSSG) + glutathione (GSH) = protein-thiol (PSH) + glutathione disulfide (GSSG). The reaction may proceed via a 'monothiol' or 'dithiol' mechanism.

label.value: histone H3K deacetylase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: histone H3 N6-acetyl-L-lysine + H2O = histone H3 L-lysine + acetate. This reaction represents the removal of an acetyl group from a histone H3.

label.value: histone H4K deacetylase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: histone H4 N6-acetyl-L-lysine + H2O = histone H4 L-lysine + acetate. This reaction represents the removal of an acetyl group from a histone H4.

label.value: histone H3 demethylase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the removal of a methyl group from a modified lysine residue of the histone H3 protein. This is a dioxygenase reaction that is dependent on Fe(II) and 2-oxoglutarate.

label.value: histone H2A ubiquitin ligase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of ubiquitin to a histone H2A substrate.

label.value: histone H2B ubiquitin ligase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of ubiquitin to a histone H2B substrate.

label.value: histone H3 ubiquitin ligase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of ubiquitin to a histone H3 substrate.

label.value: histone H4 ubiquitin ligase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of ubiquitin to a histone H4 substrate.

label.value: histone H3 arginine deiminase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + histone H3 L-arginyl = histone H3 L-citrullyl + NH4+, resulting in histone H3 citrullination.

label.value: histone H4 demethylase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the removal of a methyl group from a modified lysine residue of the histone H4 protein. This is a dioxygenase reaction that is dependent on Fe(II) and 2-oxoglutarate.

label.value: symbiont-mediated disruption of host antimicrobial peptide activity

value.value: Any process in which a symbiont interferes with a host antimicrobial peptide, for example by cleavage or degradation.

label.value: disruption of anatomical structure in another organism

value.value: The disruption of an anatomical structure of another organism, leading to damage or temporary subversion of that structure.

label.value: disruption of cell in another organism

value.value: The disruption of a cell of another organism, leading to damage or temporary subversion of that cell.

label.value: disruption of tissue in another organism

value.value: The disruption of a tissue of another organism, leading to damage or temporary subversion of that tissue.
